<p>I want to write a script, which opens the COM1-port on a PLC. Than there will be Stings send, with the syntax "1234TAB5678TAB...." and so on.</p>  <p>I wrote a script, which gets the up to 10 characters correctly, but if there are more, some bytes will be lost and/or a timeout will be created. </p>  <p>This is my code:</p>  <pre><code>Sub Main  SetVariableValue(VAR_ALL_ERR_TRASM, 0) SetVariableValue(VAR_ALL_TIMEOUT, 0) SetVariableValue(VAR_DATA, "")  ' Reset Input Buffer objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) = 0  Do          If objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) &gt; 0 Then          ' Setting Time of sending message         SendTime = Now                  ' predisposition for reading the whole input buffer                 objIOPort.IOInputLen(lPortID) = 0                  ' Waiting the whole response from serial port                 Do                     DoEvents                 Loop Until objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) &gt;= 4 Or     Now &gt; DateAdd("s",TIMEOUT,SendTime)                  If objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) &gt;= 4 Then                     ' Reading the data from Input buffer                     InString = objIOPort.IOInput(lPortID, False)                     If VerifyData(InString) Then                         'Set Movicon Variable                         SetVariableValue(VAR_DATA, InString)                         'Split InString and filter Tabs                         sBufferIn = Split(InString, vbTab)                         ' Reset of DATA Error ALARM variable                         SetVariableValue(VAR_ALL_ERR_TRASM, 0)                         SetVariableValue(VAR_ALL_TIMEOUT, 0)                          objIOPort.IOOutput(lPortID,vbCrLf &amp; "OK")                         ''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''                         objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) = 0                         ''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''                     Else                          'Set of DATA ERROR ALARM variable                         SetVariableValue(VAR_ALL_ERR_TRASM, 1)                         objIOPort.IOOutput(lPortID,vbCrLf &amp; "Error:Data")                         '''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''                         objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) = 0                         '''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''                     End If                 Else                     'Set of DATA ERROR ALARM variable                     SetVariableValue(VAR_ALL_TIMEOUT, 1)                     objIOPort.IOOutput(lPortID,vbCrLf &amp; "Error:Timeout")                     ''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''                     objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) = 0                     ''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''                 End If         ' Reset Input Buffer         objIOPort.IOInBufferCount(lPortID) = 0     End If      If bSendMessage Then         ' Enter the operations for the set and sending characters         ' In this case it sends an array of 8 bytes containing 8 characters         sBufferOut(0)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00001") '&amp;H30         sBufferOut(1)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00002") '&amp;H31         sBufferOut(2)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00003") '&amp;H32         sBufferOut(3)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00004") '&amp;H33         sBufferOut(4)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00005") '&amp;H34         sBufferOut(5)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00006") '&amp;H35         sBufferOut(6)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00007") '&amp;H36         sBufferOut(7)= GetVariableValue("DataToSend:VAR00008") '&amp;H37          objIOPort.IOOutput(lPortID, sBufferOut)         bSendMessage = False     End If        DoEvents Loop Until IsInStoppingMode  End Sub </code></pre>